<hr>

<p>There are three ways you can markup a button. An anchor, button or input element. BaseWeb tries to style buttons the same, regardless of the method you use to mark them up.</p>

<pre><code>&lt;a class=&quot;btn&quot; href=&quot;#&quot; role=&quot;button&quot;&gt;Button&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;button class=&quot;btn&quot; type=&quot;submit&quot;&gt;Button&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;input class=&quot;btn&quot; type=&quot;button&quot; value=&quot;Button&quot;&gt;</code></pre>

<div class="demo">
  <p>
    <a class="btn" href="#" role="button">Button</a>
    <button class="btn" type="submit">Button</button>
    <input class="btn" type="button" value="Button">
  </p>
</div>

